---
export const prerender = true;
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<title>Orient — Use cases for humans and machines</title>
<meta name="description" content="How teams and agents put Orient to work: a thinking and communicating space for people, a meaning layer for enterprise AI, and the loop between them." />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Spectral:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/orient.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/landing.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/usecases.css?v=11" />

{import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID && (
  <>
    <script async src={`https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=${import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID}`}></script>
    <script is:inline define:vars={{ gaId: import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID }}>
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', gaId);
    </script>
  </>
)}

</head>
<body class="uc-page">

<!-- ============ HEADER ============ -->
<header class="site-header" id="header">
  <div class="wrap bar">
    <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Orient — home">
      <img src="/logo.svg" alt="Orient" class="brand-logo" />
    </a>
    <nav class="site-nav">
      <a href="/">What is Orient</a>
      <a href="/forhumans">For Humans</a>
      <a href="/formachines">For Machines</a>
      <a href="#top" aria-current="page" style="color:var(--ink)">Use cases</a>
      <a href="/about">About</a>
    </nav>
    <button class="btn" data-scroll="#access">Request access</button>
  </div>
</header>

<main id="top">

  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="uc-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow clay">Use cases</span>
      <h1>How <span class="hu">people</span> and <span class="ma">agents</span> put Orient to work.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Orient is a meaning system for organisations — it helps people and AI systems work from the same understanding: what is <b>true</b>, what is <b>supported</b>, what is <b>contested</b>, what has been <b>decided</b>, and what remains <b>open</b>. Here is what that looks like in practice.</p>
      <figure class="uc-herodiagram reveal" role="img" aria-label="People feed judgement into Orient's meaning layer and agents act from it — both working from one shared understanding: what is true, supported, contested, decided and open.">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 960 456" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <defs>
            <marker id="ahH" markerWidth="12" markerHeight="12" refX="7" refY="5" orient="auto" markerUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
              <path d="M1.5,1.5 L8,5 L1.5,8.5" fill="none" stroke="var(--human)" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </marker>
            <marker id="ahM" markerWidth="12" markerHeight="12" refX="7" refY="5" orient="auto" markerUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
              <path d="M1.5,1.5 L8,5 L1.5,8.5" fill="none" stroke="var(--machine)" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </marker>
            <marker id="ahW" markerWidth="12" markerHeight="12" refX="7" refY="5" orient="auto" markerUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
              <path d="M1.5,1.5 L8,5 L1.5,8.5" fill="none" stroke="var(--ink-3)" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- work flowing in -->
          <text x="480" y="40" text-anchor="middle" class="d-lab">The work people &amp; AI create</text>
          <line class="conn-work" x1="480" y1="58" x2="480" y2="114" marker-end="url(#ahW)"/>

          <!-- side connectors: judgement in / action out — both directions -->
          <line class="conn-h" x1="236" y1="240" x2="352" y2="240" marker-start="url(#ahH)" marker-end="url(#ahH)"/>
          <line class="conn-m" x1="608" y1="240" x2="724" y2="240" marker-start="url(#ahM)" marker-end="url(#ahM)"/>

          <!-- flow dots: work falling in -->
          <g class="d-flow">
            <circle r="3.6" cx="480" fill="var(--ink-3)"><animate attributeName="cy" values="60;112" dur="2.1s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.18;0.82;1" dur="2.1s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
            <circle r="3.6" cx="480" fill="var(--ink-3)"><animate attributeName="cy" values="60;112" dur="2.1s" begin="-0.7s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.18;0.82;1" dur="2.1s" begin="-0.7s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
            <circle r="3.6" cx="480" fill="var(--ink-3)"><animate attributeName="cy" values="60;112" dur="2.1s" begin="-1.4s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.18;0.82;1" dur="2.1s" begin="-1.4s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
          </g>

          <!-- flow dots: humans -> meaning (judgement in) -->
          <g class="d-flow">
            <circle r="4" cy="240" fill="var(--human)"><animate attributeName="cx" values="240;348" dur="2.4s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
            <circle r="4" cy="240" fill="var(--human)"><animate attributeName="cx" values="240;348" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
          </g>
          <!-- flow dots: meaning -> humans (probes back) -->
          <g class="d-flow">
            <circle r="3.2" cy="240" fill="var(--human)" opacity="0.55"><animate attributeName="cx" values="348;240" dur="2.4s" begin="-0.6s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;0.55;0.55;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" begin="-0.6s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
            <circle r="3.2" cy="240" fill="var(--human)" opacity="0.55"><animate attributeName="cx" values="348;240" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;0.55;0.55;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
          </g>

          <!-- flow dots: meaning -> agents (action out) -->
          <g class="d-flow">
            <circle r="4" cy="240" fill="var(--machine)"><animate attributeName="cx" values="612;720" dur="2.4s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
            <circle r="4" cy="240" fill="var(--machine)"><animate attributeName="cx" values="612;720" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;1;1;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
          </g>
          <!-- flow dots: agents -> meaning (results back) -->
          <g class="d-flow">
            <circle r="3.2" cy="240" fill="var(--machine)" opacity="0.55"><animate attributeName="cx" values="720;612" dur="2.4s" begin="-0.6s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;0.55;0.55;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" begin="-0.6s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
            <circle r="3.2" cy="240" fill="var(--machine)" opacity="0.55"><animate attributeName="cx" values="720;612" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/><animate attributeName="opacity" values="0;0.55;0.55;0" keyTimes="0;0.15;0.85;1" dur="2.4s" begin="-1.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/></circle>
          </g>

          <!-- meaning core -->
          <circle class="ring-faint" cx="480" cy="240" r="142"/>
          <circle class="ring-l" cx="480" cy="240" r="120"/>
          <g class="uc-orbit">
            <circle cx="480" cy="120" r="6" fill="var(--human)"/>
            <circle cx="540" cy="136" r="4" fill="var(--machine)"/>
            <circle cx="600" cy="240" r="5" fill="var(--machine)"/>
            <circle cx="540" cy="344" r="4.5" fill="var(--ink-3)"/>
            <circle cx="420" cy="344" r="4" fill="var(--machine)"/>
            <circle cx="360" cy="240" r="5" fill="var(--human)"/>
            <circle cx="420" cy="136" r="4.5" fill="var(--human)"/>
          </g>
          <circle class="core-disc" cx="480" cy="240" r="98"/>
          <path d="M480 196 L442 238 L480 280 Z" fill="var(--human)" transform="translate(0,2)"/>
          <path d="M480 196 L518 238 L480 280 Z" fill="var(--machine)" transform="translate(0,2)"/>
          <path d="M480 196 L518 238 L480 280 L442 238 Z" fill="none" stroke="var(--paper-on-ink)" stroke-width="1.6" transform="translate(0,2)"/>
          <text x="480" y="310" text-anchor="middle" class="d-core">Meaning</text>

          <!-- humans node -->
          <rect class="node-h" x="44" y="200" width="184" height="80" rx="18"/>
          <text x="136" y="234" text-anchor="middle" class="d-title">Humans</text>
          <text x="136" y="258" text-anchor="middle" class="d-sub d-h">Think &amp; communicate</text>

          <!-- agents node -->
          <rect class="node-m" x="732" y="200" width="184" height="80" rx="18"/>
          <text x="824" y="234" text-anchor="middle" class="d-title">Agents</text>
          <text x="824" y="258" text-anchor="middle" class="d-sub d-m">Act</text>

          <!-- meaning states -->
          <text x="480" y="424" text-anchor="middle" class="d-states">true<tspan class="sep"> · </tspan>supported<tspan class="sep"> · </tspan>contested<tspan class="sep"> · </tspan>decided<tspan class="sep"> · </tspan>open</text>
        </svg>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ TWO PRODUCTS ============ -->
  <section class="section uc-intro">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Two connected products</span>
        <h2>One meaning system. Two kinds of work.</h2>
        <p>Together they form a shared meaning operating system: humans create the meaning, machines consume and operationalise it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="uc-products reveal">
        <div class="uc-prod h">
          <div class="tag">Orient for Humans</div>
          <h3>A thinking and communicating space for teams.</h3>
          <p>People capture knowledge, resolve questions, create frames, communicate clearly, and measure understanding.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-prod m">
          <div class="tag">Orient for Machines</div>
          <h3>A meaning layer for agents and enterprise AI.</h3>
          <p>Machines get structured access to the organisation's living understanding, so they reason, generate, brief, coordinate, and act with context.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FOR HUMANS ============ -->
  <section class="section uc-human" id="humans">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow clay">Orient for Humans</span>
        <h2>Turn scattered material into meaning that holds.</h2>
        <p>A knowledge base stores information. Orient helps teams think <em>with</em> it — asking what is true, what is supported, what is contested, what we have decided, and what still needs explaining.</p>
      </div>
      <figure class="ph uc-shot uc-lead reveal">
        <div class="ph-box">
          <img src="screenshots/workspace.png" alt="The Orient workspace — a team's activity, frames, resolved answers and questions in one space" />
        </div>
        <figcaption class="ph-cap" style="margin-top:16px">A team's knowledge, questions and framed work — resolved in one space.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="uc-grid reveal">
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">01</div>
          <h4>Team thinking space</h4>
          <p>One calm space to think through strategy, product, a customer problem or a board question — instead of scattering it across Slack, docs, decks and email.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">02</div>
          <h4>Capturing knowledge &amp; sources</h4>
          <p>Bring in documents, research, transcripts, feedback and links. Orient turns them into usable context — extracting themes, surfacing contradictions, connecting sources to questions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">03</div>
          <h4>Resolving important questions</h4>
          <p>Move from raw material to a considered position — supported by evidence, with the uncertainty and weak spots made visible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">04</div>
          <h4>Creating frames</h4>
          <p>Turn understanding into something communicable: a presentation, explainer, memo, briefing, podcast, training module or Q&amp;A space.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">05</div>
          <h4>Strategy &amp; leadership alignment</h4>
          <p>Capture the evidence behind strategic choices, record decisions and track what is still open — especially when strategy isn't yet simple or settled.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">06</div>
          <h4>Product &amp; roadmap reasoning</h4>
          <p>Connect feedback, evidence and strategy so the team understands <em>why</em> something is being built — not just that it's a ticket.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">07</div>
          <h4>Sales enablement &amp; positioning</h4>
          <p>Keep sales aligned with the company's current truth: accurate positioning, live proof points, objection handling and approved claims.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">08</div>
          <h4>Internal communication</h4>
          <p>Explain complex change clearly — and anticipate the confusion and objections before they spread.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">09</div>
          <h4>Learning &amp; comprehension</h4>
          <p>Measure whether people actually understood — see where knowledge landed, where it failed to propagate, and who is still confused.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">10</div>
          <h4>Board &amp; investor preparation</h4>
          <p>Resolve the narrative, surface weak assumptions, generate board frames and prepare the likely Q&amp;A.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">11</div>
          <h4>Research &amp; insight synthesis</h4>
          <p>Turn large bodies of material into structured understanding — themes, contradictions, missing evidence and unresolved probes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">12</div>
          <h4>Organisational memory</h4>
          <p>Remember not just documents but meaning: why a decision was made, what evidence mattered, what was uncertain, and what remains unresolved.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ HUMAN MOMENT (voice) ============ -->
  <section class="section uc-voice">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="uc-voice-grid">
        <figure class="ph tall reveal">
          <div class="ph-box">
            <img src="/photos/portrait.jpg" alt="A team member working with Orient" style="object-position: 24% center" />
          </div>
        </figure>
        <div class="reveal">
          <blockquote>"The work was never the hard part. Keeping everyone — and now every agent — working from the <span class="em">same understanding</span> was. That's what Orient gives us."</blockquote>
          <div class="who"><b>What teams tell us</b> · on working with Orient</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FOR MACHINES ============ -->
  <section class="section uc-machine" id="machines">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow slate">Orient for Machines</span>
        <h2>Structured meaning agents can act on.</h2>
        <p>Agents need more than documents. They need to know what is true, supported, contested, decided, outdated — and what they are allowed to say.</p>
      </div>
      <figure class="uc-machinediagram uc-lead reveal" role="img" aria-label="Orient's meaning layer structures context — true, supported, contested, decided, outdated, and what agents are allowed to say — and grounds agents over an API so they act with context.">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 960 400" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <defs>
            <marker id="mdA" markerWidth="12" markerHeight="12" refX="7" refY="5" orient="auto" markerUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
              <path d="M1.5,1.5 L8,5 L1.5,8.5" fill="none" stroke="oklch(0.7 0.08 252)" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- meaning layer source -->
          <path d="M110 178 L90 200 L110 222 Z" fill="var(--human)"/>
          <path d="M110 178 L130 200 L110 222 Z" fill="var(--machine)"/>
          <path d="M110 178 L130 200 L110 222 L90 200 Z" fill="none" stroke="var(--paper-on-ink)" stroke-width="1.4"/>
          <text x="110" y="250" text-anchor="middle" class="md-srclab">Meaning layer</text>

          <!-- connector: structures -->
          <text x="225" y="190" text-anchor="middle" class="md-conn-lab">Structures</text>
          <line class="md-conn" x1="150" y1="200" x2="296" y2="200" marker-end="url(#mdA)"/>

          <!-- structured context panel -->
          <rect class="md-panel" x="300" y="56" width="360" height="324" rx="20"/>
          <text x="480" y="96" text-anchor="middle" class="md-title">Structured context</text>

          <circle class="md-dot-pos" cx="338" cy="143" r="5.5"/>
          <text x="356" y="148" class="md-field">True</text>
          <circle class="md-dot-pos" cx="338" cy="179" r="5.5"/>
          <text x="356" y="184" class="md-field">Supported</text>
          <circle class="md-dot-warn" cx="338" cy="215" r="5.5"/>
          <text x="356" y="220" class="md-field">Contested</text>
          <circle class="md-dot-dec" cx="338" cy="251" r="5.5"/>
          <text x="356" y="256" class="md-field">Decided</text>
          <circle class="md-dot-old" cx="338" cy="287" r="5"/>
          <text x="356" y="292" class="md-field old"><tspan class="md-strike">Outdated</tspan></text>

          <line x1="324" y1="316" x2="636" y2="316" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.14)" stroke-width="1"/>

          <!-- guardrail: what they're allowed to say -->
          <rect class="md-guard" x="324" y="332" width="312" height="34" rx="10"/>
          <g class="md-guard-ico">
            <rect x="343" y="347" width="13" height="10" rx="2"/>
            <path d="M345.5 347 v-2.5 a4 4 0 0 1 8 0 v2.5"/>
          </g>
          <text x="368" y="353" class="md-guard-lab">What they're allowed to say</text>

          <!-- connector: grounds -->
          <text x="708" y="190" text-anchor="middle" class="md-conn-lab">Grounds · API</text>
          <line class="md-conn" x1="660" y1="200" x2="756" y2="200" marker-end="url(#mdA)"/>

          <!-- agents node -->
          <rect class="md-node" x="760" y="166" width="180" height="74" rx="18"/>
          <text x="850" y="200" text-anchor="middle" class="md-node-t">Agents</text>
          <text x="850" y="223" text-anchor="middle" class="md-node-s">Act with context</text>
        </svg>
        <figcaption class="md-cap">Agents grounded in the organisation's live understanding.</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="uc-grid reveal">
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">01</div>
          <h4>Agent grounding</h4>
          <p>Give agents the current organisational context before they act — the answer, the evidence, the confidence level, and what not to say.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">02</div>
          <h4>Decision memory</h4>
          <p>Tell agents <em>why</em> decisions were made — rationale, evidence, rejected alternatives, owner, and the conditions to revisit them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">03</div>
          <h4>Open probes as work queues</h4>
          <p>Expose unresolved questions as structured work agents can investigate — then route proposed answers back to humans for judgement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">04</div>
          <h4>Machine-readable company truth</h4>
          <p>A current, queryable version of what the company believes — positioning, pricing, roadmap, claims and decision boundaries.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">05</div>
          <h4>Approved claims &amp; safe generation</h4>
          <p>Ground generated content in approved meaning, so output isn't just fluent — it's organisationally safe.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">06</div>
          <h4>Search beyond documents</h4>
          <p>Return understanding, not ten files: the current logic, the supporting evidence, the live objections, and what can be said externally.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">07</div>
          <h4>Workflow automation with context</h4>
          <p>Give automations semantic context, so they act from meaning — related risks, prior accounts, affected frames — not just event data.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">08</div>
          <h4>Agent-to-human briefing</h4>
          <p>Surface what changed, what resolved, which probes remain open, where comprehension is weak, and which narratives are drifting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">09</div>
          <h4>Comprehension-aware agents</h4>
          <p>Know not just what was communicated but what was understood — and generate clearer explanations where understanding failed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">10</div>
          <h4>Narrative &amp; communication agents</h4>
          <p>Generate decks, memos, updates and customer answers grounded in the company's current understanding — aligned, not generic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">11</div>
          <h4>Multi-agent coordination</h4>
          <p>Give every agent a shared meaning layer, so sales, product, support and research don't fork into competing versions of the truth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="uc-card">
          <div class="num">12</div>
          <h4>Meaning APIs for enterprise AI</h4>
          <p>Expose resolved answers, probes, frames, decisions, evidence and confidence through APIs — so Orient sits beneath many AI surfaces.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ THE LOOP ============ -->
  <section class="section uc-loop">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="three reveal">Human <span class="hu">judgement</span> in. Machine <span class="ma">action</span> out. Shared understanding between them.</p>
      <p class="sub reveal">Humans capture knowledge and resolve questions. Orient structures the meaning and remembers the reasoning. Machines consume it to brief, generate, coordinate and act — then surface new probes for humans to judge.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ COMBINED USE CASES ============ -->
  <section class="section uc-combined">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Humans + machines</span>
        <h2>The strongest value is the loop.</h2>
        <p>Humans provide judgement. Machines consume, extend, test and act on it. These are the systems that emerge when both use Orient together.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="uc-combos reveal">
        <div class="uc-combo">
          <div class="ct"><span class="cn">01</span><h4>Strategy operating system</h4></div>
          <div class="sides">
            <div class="side h">
              <div class="role">Human side</div>
              <p>Leadership captures sources, debates options, resolves key questions, and communicates the direction.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="side m">
              <div class="role">Machine side</div>
